# archive.nonparallel.io – Creative Hub Rulebook

## Purpose
The rules in this file define how we design, build, and organize the **archive.nonparallel.io** web-platform.  This site is the single shareable link for Bryton Zoz's purely creative output (music + fashion) and is **distinct** from [bryton.studio](mdc:bryton.studio) (technical portfolio).

## Information Architecture
1.  **Two Primary Pillars** (top-level nav & URL namespaces):
    • `/music`  – showcases self-hosted/indie distribution portals.
    • `/fashion` – showcases streaming/e-commerce fashion projects.

2.  **Project Cards** (reusable React component)
    • Title, short blurb, tags (platform / type / year)
    • Hero visual (auto-pulled og:image or local thumbnail)
    • Actions:  "Visit Site", "Watch", "Listen", etc.
    • Optional Embed (audio player, video, iframe) when CORS allows.

3.  **Current Sources**
    Music
    ```yaml
    - name: Just A Reminder To Live Life
      url: https://justaremindertolivelife.com
      type: procedural-mixtape
      status: live
    - name: The Archive (Music)
      url: https://nonparallel.wixstudio.com/archive
      type: multi-purpose stream
      status: beta
    ```
    Fashion
    ```yaml
    - name: Loopless Collection (Episodes)
      url: https://nonparallel.wixstudio.com/archive/thearchive-fashion-1
      type: video-series
      status: live
    - name: Scrapwrk Store
      url: https://scrapwrk.com
      type: ecommerce
      status: alpha
    ```
    • Add new items by extending the YAML in `data/projects.yml`.

## Design Language
* **Style Reference**: iOS 26 concept guidelines – glass-morphism + spatial UI.
* **Visual Traits**: liquid-glass surfaces, blurred translucency, high-saturation gradients.
* **Shape System**: 4-point grid, **12 px radius** default, pill buttons, bubbly badges.
* **Typography**: 
  – Display: SF Pro Rounded / alternative rounded grotesque.
  – Body: Inter 1.9 rem line-height.
* **Motion**: springy ease-out animations (200–400 ms), hover lift (Z translate 4 px).  Disable if `prefers-reduced-motion`.
* **Color Palette** (HSL):
  – Neon Coral h6° s85% l60%  
  – Electric Azure h198° s100% l53%  
  – Citrine h57° s100% l55%  
  – Deep Charcoal h220° s15% l12% (background)

## Tech Stack & Repo Conventions
* **Framework**: Next.js 14 (app-router).  Directory `/apps/archive`.
* **Styling**: Tailwind CSS with custom preset `tailwind.preset.js` for the palette above.
* **Component Library**: Shadcn/ui fork with rounded-glass variants.
* **State/Content**: Projects pulled from `/data/projects.yml` via FS or CMS.
* **CI**: Vercel preview deployments on PR.

## Development Workflow
1. Add/modify project in `data/projects.yml` → run `yarn dev` to hot-reload.
2. Ensure each project has a 1200×630 og:image in `/public/og/`.
3. Write an accompanying MDX file in `/content/projects/` for deep-dive pages.
4. Accessibility pass (Lighthouse ≥ 90) before merging.

## Branding Assets
* Logo word-mark `archive.nonparallel` (lowercase, medium weight) with glass-bubble background.
* Favicon `favicon.svg`  — stylised "⟲" arrow loop symbolizing archive.

## External Links & Tracking
* Use `target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"`.
* Simple analytics via Vercel Web Analytics, no cookies.

## Future-proofing
* Provide dark-&-light themes (auto via `prefers-color-scheme`).
* Modular section to plug in **games**, **AR try-on**, or other media.

